essive inflammation and contribute to the development of various diseases, including autoimmune disorders, cancer, and inflammatory conditions. \n\nResearch continues to explore the diverse functions and upstream regulators of IκB, highlighting its importance in maintaining cellular homeostasis and responding to environmental challenges. The protein’s ability to dynamically control NF-κB activity makes it a key target in therapeutic strategies aimed at modulating inflammatory responses and treating diseases associated with chronic inflammation."}, "metrics": {"attempted_request_count": 1, "successful_response_count": 0, "failed_response_count": 0, "responses_with_tokens": 1, "prompt_tokens": 166, "completion_tokens": 385, "total_tokens": 551, "compute_duration_seconds": 121.12436294555664, "streaming_responses": 0, "retries": 0, "requests_with_retries": 0}}}